        <h1>Prayer of Peace: Relief & Resistance in Burma's War Zones</h1>
        <p> 30 minutes - High Definition - On the front line of conflict deep 
          inside Burma this documentary follows ethnic relief workers as they 
          aid internally displaced people suffering under the Burma Army. Focusing 
          on a female medic and a pastor/human rights cameraman, the film reveals 
          a people that have maintained their dignity and hope for peace despite 
          the odds. </p>
        <p> The new film "Prayer of Peace: Relief & Resistance in Burma's War 
          Zones" will screen Tuesday October 2nd at 7:30 pm at the Alliance Francaise 
          in Chiang Mai, Thailand on 138 Charoen Prathet Road. 
        <p>There will also be a screening in Bangkok, Tuesday October 9th at 8pm 
          at the Foreign Correspondents Club of Thailand. The FCCT is located 
          on the Penthouse floor of the Maneeya Center, 518/5 Ploenchit Road. 
        <h3>From the filmmaker: </h3>
        <p> "At both screenings there will be a discussion afterwards with me, 
          a Free Burma Rangers relief team member, and someone from the Thai community. 
          Thank you to everyone who is helping to make these things happen. I 
          sincerely appreciate your help. And I truly hope through our efforts 
          we are helping our friends in Burma in some way." 
        <p> DVDs will be available from Silkworm Books. 
        <p> http://frontfilms.com<br>
          http://blog.frontfilms.com 
        <p>&nbsp; 
