              <h3>About CCB</h3>
              <p> <span class="smalltext">CCB works to support the people of Burma 
                through prayer, evangelism, advocacy and action. CCB's belief 
                is that God's love is alive in Burma and its light will not be 
                put out. Though the people are suffering under an oppressive dictatorship, 
                they have not given up. We have experienced the love and redemption 
                of Jesus Christ and want to share this as the Lord leads and opens 
                hearts. </span>
              <p><span class="smalltext">Each year the CCB coordinates the Global 
                Day of Prayer for Burma. On the second Sunday of March, CCB invites 
                people around the world to pray and take action for the people 
                of Burma. Throughout the year the CCB produces newsletters and 
                information updates on the situation in Burma. For the Global 
                Day of Prayer for Burma, CCB coordinates global prayer and advocacy 
                activities as well as providing resources for those who participate. 
                Holistic support in both Thailand and Burma are coordinated through 
                CCB. CCB website: www.prayforburma.org </span> 
